The idea is VM1 in one server and VM2 in another server.

Two hardcoded things:
    1) VFIO device id (for Uddhav 01:00.2) (for Egore 01:00.3)
    2) You also need  your public ssh key in make-cloudinit script file
        such as,
        ssh_authorized_keys:
              - <your public ssh key>
    3)   -netdev user,id=net0,hostfwd=tcp::<unique port>-:22 \ (unique port for uddhav 2222, and Egor 22222)



This whole VM should be run inside a privileged container like rex-kernel.

Steps to follow
    1) make docker
    2) make enter-docker (you enter inside docker. docker has volume mounted your vm1 directory)
    3) go to images directory, run download-img-vm2.sh script
    4) go to scripts directory, and run make-cloudinit-vm2.bash script
    5) Then from scripts directory, execute launch-vm2.bash
    6) provide rosa/rosalab login
    7) lspci and ip a check bus number (e..g, from 01:04.3, 04 part is bus number, so choose ens<bus_number> interface)
    8) Assign static IP and 9000 MTU for SR-IOV VFIO nic inside VM
        sudo ip addr add 192.168.1.2/29 dev ens4  (for Egor use 192.168.10.2)
        sudo ip link set ens4 mtu 9000
        sudo ip link set ens4 up
    9) Clone the github repo again for benchmarking.

Note: don't use same ip that is used by host.
